thin_plate_axial_compression_3d.png.description: 3D diagram of thin plate subjected to axial compression showing coordinate system (x,y,z), distributed axial force Nxx on top and bottom edges, dimension labels (a, b), and force vectors

simply_supported_plate_axial_load.png.description: 3D diagram of simply-supported plate panel subjected to axial compression showing distributed load Nxx on edges, coordinate system (x,y,z), and dimension labels (a, b)

buckling_load_vs_aspect_ratio_graph.png.description: Graph showing buckling load parameter (Nxx b²/D π²) versus aspect ratio (r = a/b) with multiple curves for different mode numbers (m=1,2,3,4) showing minima at integer values

square_buckling_patterns_plates.png.description: Two rectangular plate diagrams showing buckling mode patterns with square buckles for r=2 and r=3, illustrating different buckling configurations with dimension labels (a, b)

coincident_buckling_modes_graph.png.description: Graph showing buckling load parameter (Nxx b²/D π²) versus aspect ratio r with curves for m=1,2,3 showing two coincident buckling modes at points A and B

boundary_condition_comparison_graph.png.description: Graph showing normalized buckling load versus aspect ratio r with two curves labeled CCCC and SSSS representing different boundary conditions, asymptotically approaching value of 4

plate_biaxial_compression.png.description: 3D diagram of plate panel under biaxial compression showing applied forces Nxx, Nyy on all edges with arrows indicating compression in both directions

biaxial_buckling_interaction_curve.png.description: Interaction curve showing relationship between Nxx and Nyy buckling loads with curved line in first quadrant

loading_condition_interaction_diagram.pn.description: Interaction diagram showing points A, B, C, D with vectors representing different loading conditions and aspect ratios (r=1, r=2) for buckling analysis

buckling_patterns_four_quadrants.png.description: Four small diagrams showing plate buckling patterns under different loading conditions with hatched edges indicating support/load directions arranged in quadrants around Nxx-Nyy axes

combined_loading_interaction_curve.png.description: Interaction curve for combined loading showing pure shear, pure compression, and intermediate states with Nxx and Nyy axes

compression_shear_buckling_patterns.png.description: Multiple rectangular plate diagrams showing buckling patterns for pure compression (square buckles) and pure shear (skewed buckles at ~35° angle) with contour lines, plus combined loading patterns labeled A and B

symmetric_buckling_comparison.png.description: Two small rectangular diagrams showing symmetric buckling patterns with arrows indicating loading directions and buckle orientations

tensile_load_buckling_interaction.png.description: Interaction curve showing points A and B with axes Nxx and Nyy, illustrating effect of tensile loads on buckling behavior with curved line in first quadrant
